Sorry for the delay in responding to this.  Firefox does not fire the `offline` and `online` events in the way that other browsers do.  You can test this by running this Fiddle with your console open and disconnecting your internet connection: http://jsfiddle.net/L507acnc/

In Firefox, we get no events, in Chrome, we get the events we need.  This means the only way of detecting actual network status in FF is for an actual HTTP request to fail.  On the Offline homepage, there are no requests, so this never happens.  You can manually run a check though by executing `Offline.check()` in the console, and you will see it correctly update.

